# Slack Bot Development Guidelines

## Security & Authentication
- Always verify Slack request signatures using signing secret
- Store all tokens securely in environment variables (BotToken, SigningSecret, ClientSecret)
- Implement proper error handling for API failures
- Never log sensitive user data or API responses
- Use ephemeral responses for error messages to avoid channel spam

## Bot Response Patterns
- Acknowledge slash commands immediately with `ack()`
- Respond within 3 seconds for acknowledgment
- Use Slack's block kit for rich formatting
- Include loading indicators for long-running tasks (video generation)
- Provide clear error messages with next steps
- Use `response_type: "in_channel"` for successful results
- Use `response_type: "ephemeral"` for errors and help messages

## Command Handling
- Parse command text carefully and validate input format
- Provide clear usage examples in error messages
- Handle edge cases gracefully (empty input, malformed commands)
- Log command usage for monitoring and debugging

## Video Generation Workflow
- Send immediate acknowledgment of video generation request
- Provide progress updates during long-running operations
- Send video idea first, then generate actual video
- Include both video concept and download link in final response
- Handle timeouts gracefully (5-minute limit)

## Rate Limiting & Performance
- Implement exponential backoff for API calls
- Monitor API usage and costs (20 requests/day limit)
- Queue video generation requests if needed
- Use async processing for long-running tasks

## Error Handling
- Catch specific exceptions (VideoGenerationError, ValueError)
- Provide user-friendly error messages in Slack
- Log detailed errors for debugging
- Implement fallback options when primary models fail
- Never expose internal error details to users

## Code Structure
- Use type hints for better code maintainability
- Separate concerns (parsing, generation, response formatting)
- Create custom exception classes for specific error types
- Follow Python naming conventions (snake_case)
- Keep functions focused and testable